Howard J. STANSFIELD v. Alfred T. PEARSON. No. 5256. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Oct. 10, 1955. No appearance for appellant. Williamson, Cubbison & Vaughan, Kansas City, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and BRATTON and HUXMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
